<h1>From William Watson</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Plymouth [Mass.] 23 December 1775</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>The bearer Capt. Samuel Jackson comes with six prosoners, a Midshipman &amp; five Sailors put by Capt. Talbot of the Nigar Frigate on board the Brigantne Peter, which Brigtn. was taken by sd Frigate about 18 days ago, near the Island of Barmudas, and orderd into BostonThis Brigantine was Retaken last Wednesday by our people, and was brat into this PortCapt. Jackson the Bearer of this will acquaint your Excellency with the particulars, as he had a principal hand in retakeing herThis Mr Jackson is a Zealous, Active, Worthy Friend to his Country, and has been principal in takeing all the prizes which have been brought into this Port by private Vessels<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0001-ptr">1</a>Jacob Taylor a friend &amp; relative of this Mr Jackson was mate on board Capt. Martindale who was taken by the Enemy some time since (for which I am sincerely sorry) has a Large Family &amp; in poor
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-02-02-pb-0597">[597]</span>
circumstances which must suffer much unless some way can be devised for his Redemption<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0002" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0002-ptr">2</a>I am very unwilling to give your Excellency Trouble, and must ask your pardon, when I at the very earnest request of Taylors Friends &amp; unhappy Family, Ask your Excelly whether it ant possible to exchange Mr Curtis the Midshipman for Taylor, and when I entreat your Excellency to interpose in behalf of this miserable Family &amp; of an unhappy man, who has Conducted with Dignity, &amp; has been very active in the noble Cause in which we are engaged, from the begining.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0003" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> I am your Excellencys much obliged most humble Servant</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">William Watson</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>The brig <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Peter</span>, Thomas Egger, master, was carrying a cargo of salt from Portugal to New York when she was captured on 2 Dec. by the British warship <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Niger</span>, commanded by George Talbot. An American privateer recaptured the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Peter</span> on 20 December. Samuel Jackson was a merchant and a shipmaster from Plymouth.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For the capture of the armed schooner <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Washington</span> on 4 Dec., see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0503&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-02-02-0503-fn-0008#GEWN-03-02-02-0503-fn-0008" class="document">GW to Hancock, 14 Dec. 1775 (first letter), n.8</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0554-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>In a letter of 26 Dec., which Stephen Moylan apparently wrote on behalf of GW, Watson was informed that application had been made to Gen. Howe for exchange of prisoners, to which Mr Howe was silent (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>). See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0529" class="document">GW to Howe, 18 Dec.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0543" class="document">Howe to GW, 21 Dec. 1775</a>.</p>

</div>
